---
title: "getAssetOutAmount (Payment Abstraction V2)"
---
stateDiagram-v2
    direction TB
    [*] --> q_validate: receive(amountIn, assetIn, assetOut, elapsedTime)
    q_validate --> q_price_in: amountIn > 0
    q_validate --> q_revert_amount: amountIn == 0
    q_revert_amount --> [*]: revert InvalidAmount
    q_price_in --> q_check_price_in: assetInUsdPrice = _getAssetPrice(assetIn)
    q_check_price_in --> q_step1: assetInUsdPrice > 0
    q_check_price_in --> q_revert_price: assetInUsdPrice == 0
    q_revert_price --> [*]: revert InvalidPrice
    q_step1 --> q_multiplier: usdValue = mulDivUp(amountIn, assetInUsdPrice, 10^assetInDecimals)
    q_multiplier --> q_step2: priceMultiplier = startingPriceMultiplier - decayRatePerSecond * elapsedTime
    q_step2 --> q_price_out: adjustedValue = mulWadUp(usdValue, priceMultiplier)
    q_price_out --> q_check_price_out: assetOutUsdPrice = _getAssetPrice(assetOut)
    q_check_price_out --> q_step3: assetOutUsdPrice > 0
    q_check_price_out --> q_revert_price: assetOutUsdPrice == 0
    q_step3 --> [*]: return mulDivUp(adjustedValue, 10^assetOutDecimals, assetOutUsdPrice)

    note right of q_multiplier
        INV-001: priceMultiplier bounded between endingPriceMultiplier and startingPriceMultiplier
        INV-002: priceMultiplier > 0 always holds given valid config
        INV-003: All rounding operations use ceiling division (in protocol favor)
        INV-004: assetOutAmount >= 1 for all valid inputs (proven by step chain)
    end note
